### JWT Authentication Debugging

@host = https://localhost:7038
@baseUrl = {{host}}/api

### 1. Health check (should work without auth)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Login with Admin user to get token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "Admin045@gmail.com", 
    "password": "admin123"
}

### 3. Debug authentication without token
GET {{baseUrl}}/about/debug/auth

### 4. Debug authentication WITH token (replace YOUR_TOKEN with actual token from step 2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/about/debug/auth
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Test protected endpoint (should work with admin token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/about
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Debug Test",
    "description": "Testing admin authorization after debugging"
}

### 6. Test public endpoint (should always work)
GET {{baseUrl}}/about

### 7. Check current user info endpoint 
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE